article.headline: Hawaii 66, Tennessee-Martin 53
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Riley Luettgerodt had 17 points and 13 rebounds in his first career start to lead Hawaii to a 66-53 victory over Tennessee-Martin on Thursday night. Bobby Nash added 14 points and nine rebounds for the Rainbow Warriors (9-4). Zerek Knight led Tennessee-Martin (3-11) with 12 points, the only Skyhawk to score in double figures. Hawaii pulled away from Tennessee-Martin with a 14-5 run midway through the first half to lead by as many as 15 points, 26-11, with 7:21 remaining in the first. The Rainbow Warriors shot 51.4 percent from the field in the first half and led 39-26 at the break. Tennessee-Martin pulled to within nine, 43-34, on a backcourt steal and layup by Knight with 16:23 remaining in the game. But Hawaii responded with an 11-0 run of its own to go up 54-34 with 10:51 remaining. Hawaii dominated the boards, outrebounding Tennessee-Martin 45-36.
